A. E. KRISE, Receiver of The FIDELITY LAND & INVESTMENT CORPORATION, Appellant, v. UNITED STATES of America, Appellee. No. 4009. Circuit Court of Appeals, Fourth Circuit. April 23, 1936. T. J. Wool, of Norfolk, Va., for appellant. Sterling Hutcheson, U. S. Atty., of Norfolk, Va. (H. II. Holt, Jr., Asst. U. S. Ally., of Norfolk, Va., on the brief), for the United States.

Before PARKER, NORTHCOTT, and SOPER, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

The decree in this case is affirmed on the authority of Prince William County v. United States (C.C.A.) 79 F.(2d) 1007 and cases cited.

Affirmed.
